<br>
I got to 191 skill and was wary of going any further as everyone I asked said it would cost another 5 or 6 k at least to get to 250, finally said &quot;sod it&quot; and skilled to 250 making about 1.5k in the process.<br>
<br>
I enchanted every bar and had charisma at 140<br>
<br>
I basically used the next gem up to skill up - none of this &quot;well its cheaper combines&quot; as you get more fails the further away the trivial is - otherwise everyone would have the grandmaster eyeglasses. I rarely failed using this method <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I also got my eyeglass at the sametime (I wanted those weight reduction bags) I failed on my first attempt, but luckily got it on my second attempt - Apparently this is down to the RNG as I heard of someone failing 9 times - the cost of the eyeglass is definitely more of a stumbling block than skilling up to 250 itself as it costs about 5k each attempt.<br>
